# Mikhaylovka, Kizhinginsky District, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Mikhaylovka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kizhinginsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 560 as of 2010. There are 7 streets.
Geography
Mikhaylovka is located 49&nbsp;km east of Kizhinga (the district's administrative centre) by road. Mogsokhon is the nearest rural locality.
